title: Gideon the Ninth
description: Gideon the Ninth is the first book in the New York Times and USA Today Bestselling Locked Tomb Series, and one of the Best Books of 2019 according to NPR, the New York Public Library, Amazon, BookPage, Shelf Awareness, BookRiot, and Bustle! WINNER of the 2020 Locus Award and Crawford Award Finalist for the 2023 Hugo Award for Best Series! Finalist for the 2020 Hugo, Nebula, Dragon, and World Fantasy Awards.

title: Harrow the Ninth
description: Harrow the Ninth, the second book in the Locked Tomb series, follows the events of Gideon the Ninth, expanding the universe and deepening the mystery.

title: Nona the Ninth
description: Nona the Ninth is the third installment in the Locked Tomb series, continuing the thrilling saga of necromancers and political intrigue.

title: Alecto the Ninth
description: Alecto the Ninth is the final book in the Locked Tomb series, concluding the epic tale of necromancy, power struggles, and dark secrets.

title: The Priory of the Orange Tree
description: The Priory of the Orange Tree is an epic fantasy novel by Samantha Shannon, offering a standalone story filled with dragons, queens, and a world on the brink of war.

title: The Name of the Wind
description: The Name of the Wind is the first book in Patrick Rothfuss's Kingkiller Chronicle series, telling the story of a gifted young man destined for greatness.

title: The Way of Kings
description: The Way of Kings is the first book in Brandon Sanderson's Stormlight Archive series, an epic fantasy tale set in a world of storms and magic.

title: Mistborn: The Final Empire
description: Mistborn: The Final Empire is the first book in Brandon Sanderson's Mistborn series, introducing a world where ash falls from the sky and mist rules the night.

title: The Lies of Locke Lamora
description: The Lies of Locke Lamora is the first book in Scott Lynch's Gentleman Bastard series, following the adventures of a master thief in a richly detailed fantasy world.

title: The Blade Itself
description: The Blade Itself is the first book in Joe Abercrombie's First Law trilogy, a gritty and darkly humorous tale of war, politics, and betrayal.

title: The Fifth Season
description: The Fifth Season is the first book in N.K. Jemisin's Broken Earth trilogy, set in a world plagued by apocalyptic seismic events.

title: Dune
description: Dune is a science fiction masterpiece by Frank Herbert, exploring themes of politics, religion, and human nature on the desert planet of Arrakis.

title: The Hobbit
description: The Hobbit is a beloved fantasy novel by J.R.R. Tolkien, following the journey of Bilbo Baggins as he embarks on an unexpected adventure.

title: A Game of Thrones
description: A Game of Thrones is the first book in George R.R. Martin's A Song of Ice and Fire series, a tale of power, betrayal, and the struggle for the Iron Throne.

title: American Gods
description: American Gods is a dark and atmospheric novel by Neil Gaiman, blending mythology and modern-day America in a story about gods and mortals.
